evelopment at risk by under educating its rural population there is clearly a danger that the nation may fail to meet its new challenge if the average rural child does not receive an education necessary to support a modern industrial society download pdf+ reap brief 108 development challenges tuition barriers and high school education in china modified may 2010 pdf reap108 final pdf 698.1 kb topics investment china stanford university all rights reserved 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints rss+ rss xml feeds
